# Single H1 Per Page

- Every rendered page on this site must have exactly one `h1`.
- If a page layout or route component already renders the page title as `h1`, content files must not add another `#` heading.
- For blog posts, the visible page `h1` comes from frontmatter metadata rendered by `src/app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx`.
- Never add a second `h1` inside blog MDX content.

Examples:

- Bad: frontmatter title renders as `h1` and the MDX body also starts with `# Title`
- Good: frontmatter title renders the page `h1`, and the MDX body starts with an intro paragraph or `##` section
